{
  "_comment": [
    "Dispatch rule template — one room per call, routed by dialed DID to a",
    "specific agent. Uses the modern CreateSIPDispatchRuleRequest.dispatch_rule",
    "form (SIPDispatchRuleInfo). The deprecated flat-field form still works but",
    "has confusingly inverted semantics for `inbound_numbers` — don't use it.",
    "",
    "Apply with:",
    "  lk sip dispatch create config/dispatch-rule-per-call.json --trunks <trunk-id>",
    "",
    "THE TWO NUMBER FILTER FIELDS — do not confuse them:",
    "",
    "  `numbers`         — rule matches when the caller dialed one of these",
    "                      DIDs. This maps to req.CalledNumber (the TO leg).",
    "                      THIS IS THE FIELD YOU ALMOST ALWAYS WANT for per-DID",
    "                      routing.",
    "",
    "  `inbound_numbers` — rule matches when the caller's own number is in this",
    "                      list. This maps to req.CallingNumber (the FROM leg).",
    "                      Only useful if you want per-caller allowlisting at",
    "                      the rule layer. The trunk's AllowedNumbers field is",
    "                      a better place for that in most setups.",
    "",
    "We shipped with `inbound_numbers` pointed at DIDs once and every call 486'd",
    "as 'flood' (DispatchNoRuleDrop) — the livekit-sip log reason string is",
    "misleading. Keep the comment above honest.",
    "",
    "Fields to edit before applying:",
    "  - `name`                                       human-readable label",
    "  - `numbers`                                    DID(s) this rule matches on (E.164)",
    "  - `rule.dispatchRuleIndividual.roomPrefix`     rooms will be <prefix>_<caller>_<random>",
    "  - `room_config.agents[0].agentName`            which Python worker joins",
    "                                                 (phone-nyla | phone-aoi | phone-party)",
    "  - `room_config.agents[0].metadata`             JSON passed as ctx.job.metadata",
    "",
    "Docs: https://docs.livekit.io/sip/dispatch-rule/"
  ],

  "dispatch_rule": {
    "name": "twilio-to-phone-nyla",

    "numbers": [
      "+15550000000"
    ],

    "rule": {
      "dispatchRuleIndividual": {
        "roomPrefix": "phone"
      }
    },

    "room_config": {
      "agents": [
        {
          "agentName": "phone-nyla",
          "metadata": "{\"route\":\"default\",\"source\":\"sip\"}"
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
